<br>
It has been presented to you that a guild only has input on rotations for which it is involved, and the RTA admins are supposed to act as nuetral parties for guild disputes.  Establishing a rotation means that there is a conflict (in the case of a rotation, it means competition) for a boss spawn or group of boss spawns.  Using the logic of the RTA admins being the generators of a nuetral ground for which disputes may be settled, then they are perfectly within their power to create a private forum as they did.<br>
<br>
Please note in your ranting that Noble Blade wasn't in the elemental planes when the forum was made, and as far as I am aware weren't involved with its creation.<br>
<br>
Also note that while Thundaron may appear inactive from his board duties, there are duties of the rta that are dealt with outside of the forums.  For example, the private RTA channel maintainance, acting as a nuetral party in guild disputes, and a few other such activities.<br>
<br>
Nycah is a member of BotS.  Both Nycah and Thundaron were previously members of SoT and acted as admins during their tenure at that time as well.<br>
<br>
I am curious though, are there any RTA Reps that object to the Elemental Planes Forum being a private place for discussion of rotation establishment?<br>
