<br>
Fact 1:<br>
The RTA has no authority other then what players/guilds in the Rathe let it have. Verant does not authorize any of the RTA's rules or authority. Any player(s) and guild(s) can do as they wish (within the bounds of the EULA agreement) in any zone without the RTA having any power or authority whatsoever.<br>
<br>
Fact 2:<br>
The RTA guidelines that define interaction between guilds relating to sought after camps, mobs, and zones, has been largely followed for many years, and will probably continue to be.<br>
<br>
Fact 3:<br>
The large majority (if not all) guilds involved with the Rathe and the RTA, approve of the RTA guidlines and find them to be beneficial and just.<br>
<br>
Fact 4:<br>
Guild interaction regarding sought after camps, mobs and zones is much more mature and professional on the Rathe then most, if not all other servers, specifically because of the RTA rotation and underlying rules. This also allows for more efficient &quot;farming&quot; of the zones and items, as well as allowing players/people to plan their lives more effectively. The alternative of course being chaos and &quot;might defining right&quot; as the strongerst and fastest guilds overrun the smaller guilds for every opportunity.<br>
<br>
Finally:<br>
I enjoy reading the rhetoric in this thread, as compared to many of the posts that usually fill these threads it makes for more interesting and entertaining reading then what is normally found here.<br>
<br>
And Lastly:<br>
If the RTA is willing to take money from the people of these forums for it's &quot;gold&quot; status, then I suspect no forums should be hidden - unless those that pay allow for it, or agree to it.<br>
<br>
ps.<br>
<br>
There is some discussion of penalizing guilds/players that do not follow the RTA rules.<br>
<br>
Any actions of this nature could be construed as a violation of the EULA and thus technically create a scenario where some or all of the RTA could be up for banishment from The Rathe.<br>
