<br>
1) if you violate something or other, the RTA does in fact issue a penalty, typically in the form of being skipped in your 'turn' in the RTA agreed rotation.<br>
<br>
2) if you choose to ignore this, then the RTA in turn will choose to ignore you, and any attempts you make at mobs (following pnp etc yadda yadda).<br>
<br>
There really is no punishment, unless you accept it - that is, accept to be placed back on the RTA agreed sharing of spawns.  If you choose not to accept the relocation of your entity in the spawn list, that is your choice, which will basically remove you from the protection and convenience of the RTA.  You would essentially have to fight for your chance at any mob you tried to kill, and in all likelyhood no one in the RTA would be gracious about it - as you elected to become an outcast.  Sure, you would probably kill a mob or few, every now and then.  But the effort/stress involved would outweigh being under the protection of the RTA.<br>
<br>
Its not really a punishment, and imo couldnt be acted upon by SOE, GMs, or any form of pnp rules.  The 'punishment' is simply a removal of convenience (that do not exist in soe's pnp listing, because we created and agreed on them), nothing more nothing less.<br>
